cs.CR, cs.NE, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the security, privacy, and trust challenges of a new Internet paradigm that involves connecting humans bi-directionally to the net using only their brain. This involves a combination of computer science, neuroscience, and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
